**The instructions for the first declaration phase follow:**

High-Level Reasoning for the First Declaration

   A. Avoid Speculation Losses
      - If you declare a value lower than your true value, speculators can profit from buying your land (you lose half the difference).
      - If you declare a value higher than or equal to your real value, speculators would lose if they tried to buy, so they typically won’t buy at all.

   B. Encourage the Project to Win
      - Market selects Project or No Project based on the median of recent trades.
      - Public signals (influenced by initial declarations) sway share price expectations.
      - Declare near the upper bound ({{ public_information.boundaries["developer"]["projectA"]["high"] }}) to influence the Project's perceived value upward.

   C. Net Effect of Declaring Higher Values
      - Higher declarations increase {{ public_information.initial_tax_rate }}% tax, but you recoup some cost via your 30 tax shares.
      - High Project declaration discourages speculators and favors the Project being chosen.
      - No Project declaration should be just above your real value to avoid speculation losses.

Specific “First Declaration” instructions

No Project Declaration
   - Declare min({{ private_information.property.v[0] + 1 }}, {{ public_information.boundaries["developer"]["noProject"]["high"] }})

Project Declaration
   - Declare max({{ private_information.property.v[1] + 1 }}, {{ public_information.boundaries["developer"]["projectA"]["high"] }})


3. **Your Decision to Make**:
   - Declare your land value for both scenarios (Project and No Project)
   - Your declaration will affect which scenario is chosen
   - Provide the output as a JSON object:

    {
        "gameId": {{ meta.game_id }},
        "type": "declare",
        "declaration": [
            <value_no_project>,
            <value_project>,
            0,
        ],
    }

   - Replace `<value_no_project>` with your chosen declaration for “No Project.”
   - Replace `<value_project>` with your chosen declaration for “Project.”
   - The third entry is always 0 as specified.


Use these instructions exactly to minimize speculation losses while also keeping the first-declaration tax low.
